The '''D'Arcy Thompson Zoology Museum''' is a museum of [[zoology]] at the [[University of Dundee]] in Scotland.<ref name="tripadvisor">{{cite web| url=https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/Attraction_Review-g186518-d8587624-Reviews-D_Arcy_Thompson_Zoology_Museum-Dundee_Scotland.html | title=D'Arcy Thompson Zoology Museum | publisher=[[TripAdvisor]] | accessdate=30 October 2016 }}</ref> 

The museum is named after the Scottish biologist and mathematician [[D'Arcy Thompson]] (1860–1948), who founded it in the 1880s.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.list.co.uk/place/23942-darcy-thompson-zoology-museum/ | title=D'Arcy Thompson Zoology Museum | website=www.list.co.uk | publisher=The List | location=UK | accessdate=30 October 2016 }}</ref> The museum has a collection of birds, fish, insects, mammals, and reptiles from around the world, together with some of D'Arcy Thompson's models and teaching material. The museum has 27 specimens from the voyage of {{HMS|Challenger|1858|6}} of  1872–1876.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.hmschallenger.net/about/Contributing-Organisations/DArcy-Thompson-Zoology-Museum | title=D'Arcy Thompson Zoology Museum, University of Dundee Museum Services | website=www.hmschallenger.net | publisher=HMS Challenger | accessdate=30 October 2016 }}</ref>

The museum also has an art collection, including [[digital art]] of cellular forms by [[Andy Lomas]], inspired by the work of D'Arcy Thompson and funded by the UK [[Art Fund]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.dundee.ac.uk/museum/collections/zoology/renew/lomas/ | work=D'Arcy Thompson Zoology Museum Art Collection | title=Andy Lomas | publisher=[[University of Dundee]] Museum Services | location=UK | accessdate=30 October 2016 }}</ref>

